reviews.review_text:
Totally awesome recording I am so incredibly pleased to find that there is such an awesome recording from the concert they played on the day that I was born!

The recording quality is great.  Jerry and Donna are on with great vocals on The Music Never Stopped, and the song finishes with a high-energy, rockin' guitar solo.  All in all the band is tight and it's just as I wish for my music to be:
Trippy as hell, rockin' out, carrying me off into outer space where I like to go sometimes.

thanks a million to the dead, I love you guys!
Hammer In Time Man That's what Weir says at 3:25 into Jack Straw. Guess they were still fixing the drum riser! Great sound! Thanks Charlie.
4-7-78 Excellent. I love 1978 shows. Great sound quality as per usual from Charlie.
